    <h3>Styling</h3>
    <div class="row">
        <p class="descriptive col-xs-12 col-sm-8 col-lg-6">
            There are a number of helpful ways you can style icons ... colors, spins, etc.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-1">
            {{ui-icon icon='smile-o' size='lg'}} {{ui-icon icon='smile-o' muted=true size='lg'}}
        </div>
        <div class="snippet col-xs-11">
            \{{ui-icon icon='smile-o' <strong>muted=true</strong> size='lg'}} - muting drops opacity to give a muted look
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-1">
            {{ui-icon icon='smile-o' size='lg' cursor=true}} {{ui-icon icon='smile-o' muted=true size='lg' cursor=true}}
        </div>
        <div class="snippet col-xs-11">
            \{{ui-icon icon='smile-o' <strong>cursor=true</strong> size='lg'}} - setting the cursor effects <em>cursor</em> and <em>hover</em>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-xs-1">
            {{ui-icon icon='smile-o' size='lg' muted=true color='purple' cursor=true}} {{ui-icon icon='smile-o' muted=true color='green' size='lg' cursor=true}}
        </div>
        <div class="snippet col-xs-11">
            \{{ui-icon icon='smile-o' size='lg' muted=true color='purple' cursor=true}} <br/>
            muted and cursor effect <em>opacity</em> not <em>color</em>, setting colors explicitly does not interfere with "muted" or "cursor" effects
        </div>
    </div>
